linux-sidux-2.6 (2.6.24-7) unstable; urgency=low

  * update to unionfs 2.2.4.
  * use (= ${source:Version}) instead of the deprecated ${Source-Version}.
  * tighten dependencies to (= ${source:Version}) for our metapackages.
  * bump the ABI to 2.6.24.2.slh.8.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sun, 17 Feb 2008 15:40:38 +0100

linux-sidux-2.6 (2.6.24-6) unstable; urgency=low

  * add 2.6.24.2_hrtimer-fixes.diff, refresh against vanilla 2.6.24:
    - hrtimer: check relative timeouts for overflow
    - hrtimer: catch expired CLOCK_REALTIME timers early
  * add bugfix/2.6.24.2_ipw2200_fix-ucode-assertion-for-RX-queue-overrun.diff:
    Restock the RX queue when there are a lot of unused frames so that the
    RX ring buffer doesn't overrun, causing a ucode assertion.  Backport of
    patch "iwlwifi: fix ucode assertion for RX queue overrun".
  * revert blkdev for VIA and ALi to libata again, doesn't help anyways.
  * drop unused series files.
  * drop feature sets without dedicated maintainer (xen/ vserver).
  * strip disabled packages from rules.real.
  * don't confuse descriptions in debian/control.
  * remove xen templates.
  * grub or grub2 are also valid bootloaders for amd64 and i386.
  * strip rules.real from xen, s390, m68k and powerpc specifics.
  * merge patchsets confusing patch.apply.
  * import linux-2.6 changes from trunk:
    [ Bastian Blank ]
    - Move some linux specific code from
      debian/lib/python/debian_linux/gencontrol.py.
    - debian/bin/gencontrol.py: Force the existance of some values.
    [ Maximilian Attems ]
    - postinst: nuke the real user mentioned useless warn()
    - reboot warning gone waldi killed some time ago, no need to reference it.
    - postinst: Nuke confusing postinst message.
      this message generates far to many bugreports and seems pretty useless,
      so just get rid of it.
  * introduce meta packages to pull in the most recent kernels for the given
    architectures and flavours, right now this builds:
    - linux-image-2.6-sidux-amd64
      + linux-headers-2.6-sidux-amd64
    - linux-image-2.6-sidux-686
      + linux-headers-2.6-sidux-686
  * update to compat level 6.
  * really build meta packages.

 -- Stefan Lippers-Hollmann <s.l-h@gmx.de>  Sat, 16 Feb 2008 23:21:21 +0100

linux-sidux-2.6 (2.6.24-5) unstable; urgency=low

  * really disable CONFIG_PATA_VIA.

